        <h2 class="sectionHeader">What Is RSS?</h2>
        <p>I love <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/RSS">RSS</a>! RSS is the classic way of following a blog or other feed, and it's the technology behind podcasts. It's <a href="https://reillyspitzfaden.com/posts/2024/03/rss-is-nice/">a nice way to follow only the things you want</a> and avoid the algorithms of many social media sites.</p>

        <p>To follow a feed, you need an RSS reader. For desktop readers, I use <a href="https://netnewswire.com/">NetNewsWire</a> on macOS, <a href="https://apps.gnome.org/NewsFlash/">Newsflash</a> on Linux, and I've heard good things about <a href="https://github.com/yang991178/fluent-reader">Fluent Reader</a> on Windows. For mobile, I use <a href="https://netnewswire.com/">NetNewsWire</a> again on iOS, and I've heard good things about <a href="https://github.com/yanus171/Handy-News-Reader">Handy News Reader</a> and <a href="https://github.com/yang991178/fluent-reader-lite">Fluent Reader Lite</a> for Android.</p>

